page.title: 04WILD LIFE - COSHESTON AREA
page.content: The quiet countryside and creeks round Cosheston and Pembroke make it a good area for wild life.These birds have been seen on the muddy salt flats and the country near Cosheston:cormorants, blackheaded,black backed and herring gulls,mallard,oyster catchers,dunlin, crow,buzzard,heron,great crested grebe, hedge sparrow,jackdaw, great tit,blue tit,magpie,mute swan,wren, blackbird, robin,barn owl,rook,song thrush,tawny owl,widgeon,wood pigeon, swallows,house martins,redshank,green shank.These animals have also been seen:grey seal, mole, brown rat,house mice, bank voles, shrews,rabbits, foxes,badgers,weasel,hedgehogs,stoats, grey squirrels,bats.Pollution from the refineries and Power station down stream does not seem to have affected the animals and birds though some plants have been stunted.
